  "text": "The Chip Firing Game (CFG) [BL92] is defined over a directed graph. We give an example of a CFG together with its configuration space in Figure 2 . The Abelian Sandpile Model (ASM) [BTW87] is defined over an undirected graph, with a distinguished vertex called the sink and denoted by ⊥. The sink can never be fired. Finally the Chip Firing Game on a mutating graph (MCFG) [CITATION_1] is played on a directed graph that changes during the game in the following way: after the firing of a vertex, its outgoing edges are removed and new ones are added in a pre-determined way (the vertex set V remains the same). A position of a MCFG consists in:",
